-
-- (CAF-managed; populated during CAF run.)
+- Lifecycle posture: `stage_0_local_prototype` in `architecture_scaffolding`; refusal mode is fail-closed.
+- Allowed artifact classes are limited to directories, markdown docs, config stubs, non-runnable code placeholders, and TODO comments.
+- Allowed writes are constrained to the instance playbook/guardrails/caf_meta/layer_7/feedback packet surfaces and companion repo profile path.
+- Forbidden actions include generating runnable production code, claiming production readiness, changing architecture pins, or selecting vendors/providers.
+- Runtime/profile pins resolve to local Docker Compose, Python + FastAPI, Postgres, SQLAlchemy ORM, and manual composition root wiring.
+- Auth and eventing are intentionally mock-bound (`auth_mode=mock`, `eventing_backend=mock_in_memory`) for this generation phase.
+- Candidate enforcement bar keeps tests optional in this stage and explicitly forbids unresolved placeholder tokens in governed outputs.
+- UI posture is web SPA with React + shadcn in a separate UX service preference while architecture work remains spec-first.
