## Pin-derived system constraints (CAF-managed)
- Enforce immutable tenant context from ingress through all AP workflows (`pin_ref: AP-1=Ingress-Bound Context`; `pin_ref: DP-1=Logical Isolation (Enforced)`).
- Require synchronous policy checks before execution and before every side-effecting tool/action (`pin_ref: AP-3=Pre-Execution Evaluation`; `pin_ref: AI-3=Pre-Inâ€¦
- Gate agent and AI operations with explicit pre-action safety checks and reject unsafe requests fail-closed (`pin_ref: AP-4=Pre-Invocation Safety Gates`; `pin_râ€¦
- Keep agent authority policy-derived and tenant-scoped; never allow global authority escalation (`pin_ref: AI-2=Policy-Derived Authority`; `pin_ref: CP-3=Human,â€¦
- Treat the control plane as the sole lifecycle and governance authority for policy, identity, and safety gate definitions (`pin_ref: CP-2=Authoritative Lifecyclâ€¦
- Emit auditable evidence synchronously for decisions, data access, and admin-sensitive changes (`pin_ref: AI-6=Synchronous Evidence Emission`; `pin_ref: AP-6=Syâ€¦
- Persist tenant data in shared infrastructure only with tenant-keyed addressing, tenant-partitioned placement, and mandatory tenant-scoped query paths (`pin_refâ€¦
- Enforce retention/deletion and lineage obligations in the data/storage planes with policy-driven controls (`pin_ref: DP-3=Access + Retention + Lineage Enforcemâ€¦
- Support tenant-scoped backup/restore flows without exposing cross-tenant data (`pin_ref: ST-5=Tenant-Scoped Backup and Restore`).
- Keep AP and CP runtime shapes as HTTP API services and keep packaging local via Docker Compose for this phase (`pin_ref: AP-5=Agent Invocation Only`; `rail_refâ€¦
- Constrain implementation outputs to prototype-safe artifact classes and allowed write paths until lifecycle phase advances (`rail_ref: lifecycle.evolution_stagâ€¦

## Technology posture (CAF-managed)
- Lifecycle posture: `stage_0_local_prototype` in `architecture_scaffolding`; refusal mode is fail-closed.
- Allowed artifact classes are limited to directories, markdown docs, config stubs, non-runnable code placeholders, and TODO comments.
- Allowed writes are constrained to the instance playbook/guardrails/caf_meta/layer_7/feedback packet surfaces and companion repo profile path.
- Forbidden actions include generating runnable production code, claiming production readiness, changing architecture pins, or selecting vendors/providers.
- Runtime/profile pins resolve to local Docker Compose, Python + FastAPI, Postgres, SQLAlchemy ORM, and manual composition root wiring.
- Auth and eventing are intentionally mock-bound (`auth_mode=mock`, `eventing_backend=mock_in_memory`) for this generation phase.
- Candidate enforcement bar keeps tests optional in this stage and explicitly forbids unresolved placeholder tokens in governed outputs.
- UI posture is web SPA with React + shadcn in a separate UX service preference while architecture work remains spec-first.

## SPEC_SIGNAL
App-plane constraints:
- Resolve tenant context once at ingress and propagate it immutably through every application workflow (`pin_ref: AP-1=Ingress-Bound Context`).
- Perform policy evaluation and authorization checks before execution and inline with request handling (`pin_ref: AP-2=Inline Enforcement`; `pin_ref: AP-3=Pre-Exâ€¦
- Run safety-gate checks before AI/agent invocation and before side-effecting actions (`pin_ref: AP-4=Pre-Invocation Safety Gates`; `pin_ref: AI-3=Pre-Invocationâ€¦
- Limit AP responsibility to orchestrating governed agent invocations; long-lived governance state remains control-plane owned (`pin_ref: AP-5=Agent Invocation Oâ€¦
- Emit synchronous evidence for key request, decision, and publish/admin transitions (`pin_ref: AP-6=Synchronous Emission`; `pin_ref: AI-6=Synchronous Evidence Eâ€¦
- Model product capabilities around tenant-scoped widget CRUD, organization (tags/collections), sharing by role, and tenant administration from the resolved PRD.
- Keep first release intentionally limited (no cross-tenant sharing, no realtime collaboration, no complex workflow automation) to match PRD constraints.
- Honor prototype rails: no runnable production code claims, no vendor selection, and no writes outside allowed CAF instance surfaces.

## UI_SIGNAL
- ui.present: true
- ui.kind: web_spa
- ui.framework: react
- ui.deployment_preference: separate_ui_service

## UI_PRODUCT_SURFACE
- team members can create and maintain widgets
- team leads can organize and publish collections within tenant boundaries
- tenant admins can manage roles/settings with clear audit visibility
- open the widget catalog, create/edit a widget, and confirm save outcome
- organize widgets with tags and collections, then verify collection membership
- publish a collection to tenant roles and validate who can view/edit
- review activity history for widget, collection, and admin changes
- manage tenant users/roles/settings from admin surfaces
- Dashboard: recent widget activity, quick actions, and pending publication/admin signals
- Widget Catalog: searchable/sortable list with tenant-scoped filters and status
- Widget Detail and Editor: metadata + content editing with version/history access
- Collections Workspace: collection list, membership management, and publish controls

