 ## System constraints derived from the architectural intent + guardrails (CAF-managed)
 
-(Derived constraints from pins + Layer 8 resolved rails.)
+- Enforce immutable tenant context from ingress through all AP workflows (`pin_ref: AP-1=Ingress-Bound Context`; `pin_ref: DP-1=Logical Isolation (Enforced)`).
+- Require synchronous policy checks before execution and before every side-effecting tool/action (`pin_ref: AP-3=Pre-Execution Evaluation`; `pin_ref: AI-3=Pre-Invocation Evaluation Only`).
+- Gate agent and AI operations with explicit pre-action safety checks and reject unsafe requests fail-closed (`pin_ref: AP-4=Pre-Invocation Safety Gates`; `pin_ref: AI-5=Pre-Action Safety Gates`; `rail_ref: refusal_posture=fail_closed`).
+- Keep agent authority policy-derived and tenant-scoped; never allow global authority escalation (`pin_ref: AI-2=Policy-Derived Authority`; `pin_ref: CP-3=Human, Service, and Agent Identity Governance`).
+- Treat the control plane as the sole lifecycle and governance authority for policy, identity, and safety gate definitions (`pin_ref: CP-2=Authoritative Lifecycle Owner`; `pin_ref: CP-4=Centralized Policy Authoring`; `pin_ref: CP-5=Centralized Safety Gate Orchestration`).
+- Emit auditable evidence synchronously for decisions, data access, and admin-sensitive changes (`pin_ref: AI-6=Synchronous Evidence Emission`; `pin_ref: AP-6=Synchronous Emission`; `pin_ref: DP-5=Inline Evidence Emission`; `pin_ref: ST-6=Inline Evidence Emission`).
+- Persist tenant data in shared infrastructure only with tenant-keyed addressing, tenant-partitioned placement, and mandatory tenant-scoped query paths (`pin_ref: ST-1=Shared Storage with Logical Isolation`; `pin_ref: ST-2=Tenant-Keyed Primary Addressing`; `pin_ref: ST-3=Tenant-Partitioned Placement`).
+- Enforce retention/deletion and lineage obligations in the data/storage planes with policy-driven controls (`pin_ref: DP-3=Access + Retention + Lineage Enforcement`; `pin_ref: ST-4=Retention + Hard Deletion`).
+- Support tenant-scoped backup/restore flows without exposing cross-tenant data (`pin_ref: ST-5=Tenant-Scoped Backup and Restore`).
+- Keep AP and CP runtime shapes as HTTP API services and keep packaging local via Docker Compose for this phase (`pin_ref: AP-5=Agent Invocation Only`; `rail_ref: platform.packaging=docker_compose`; `rail_ref: platform.infra_target=local`).
+- Constrain implementation outputs to prototype-safe artifact classes and allowed write paths until lifecycle phase advances (`rail_ref: lifecycle.evolution_stage=stage_0_local_prototype`; `rail_ref: lifecycle.generation_phase=architecture_scaffolding`).
